@node Eigene Levelpakete, Backups, Fortgeschrittene Themen, Fortgeschrittene Themen
@section Eigene Levelpakete

@ref{Das Levelpaket-Menü} provides some additional features. The
@samp{User} group has three level packs that are initially empty:
@samp{Auto Folder}, @samp{History} and @samp{Search Result}.

By clicking on the @samp{Search} button in the level pack menu you can search in
the pool of levels. Just move the mouse to the text field and enter the string to
search. You may search within author, title and file name. The search is case 
insensitve. For example, you can search for the string ``jump''. The resulting levels will be 
provided as a level pack called ``Search Results''.

The level pack @samp{History} is updated automatically with every level you play.
This may be useful if you look for a level you played last week but do not know
the keywords to search for.

The @samp{Auto Folder} is a level pack that you can use to add new
levels, for example levels you download from the Internet or write yourself. The folder in which you should
store the levels is @samp{levels/auto} on the @samp{User Path} as shown in
@ref{Einstellungen}. Levels in this folder are automatically found and
loaded by Enigma when it starts.

Enigma provides many more useful features beyond the scope of this manual.
Please read the reference manual for more details.

@node Backups, Ergebnisse hochladen, Eigene Levelpakete, Fortgeschrittene Themen
@section Backups

If you are afraid of losing all your scores due to a hard drive
failure, or if you want to transfer your scores from one computer to
another, it is helpful to know how to back up Enigma's status
information.  To do that, first look up @samp{User Path} from Enigma's
@ref{Einstellungen} menu.  You can simply back up that folder---the
important files are @samp{enigma.score} and @samp{state.xml}.

@node Ergebnisse hochladen, Enigma updaten, Backups, Fortgeschrittene Themen
@section Ergebnisse hochladen

For registration of your scores you need to send us the @samp{enigma.score}
file located at the folder @samp{User Path}. Please look at the project
homepage for more detailed instructions.

To automatically download the updated world record score lists you just need to
enable the option @samp{Ratings Update}.

@node Enigma updaten, , Ergebnisse hochladen, Fortgeschrittene Themen
@section Enigma updaten

If you did not customize your old Enigma version simply deinstall the old
version and install the new one. That is all you have to do as your scores will
be updated automatically.

Just in case you added levels to the Enigma installation directories you have
to backup them prior deinstallation. After that you can safely deinstall the
old version and install the new one.

